    "last_activity_date" : 1728486564,
    "last_edit_date" : 1728486564,
    "creation_date" : 1724867966,
    "answer_id" : 78924686,
    "question_id" : 68473460,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you're unable to view this information via the link <a href=\"https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/access/api\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/access/api</a>, even with admin permissions (common for non-company accounts), try these alternatives:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Direct link: <a href=\"https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/access/integrations/api\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/access/integrations/api</a></li>\n<li>Xcode Cloud: Navigate to &quot;Users and Access&quot; and find the &quot;Xcode Cloud&quot; tab. The Issuer ID will be shown in the URL.</li>\n<li>HTML Inspection: Click your profile in the top-right corner. In the HTML of the account list, search for the target account's <code>data-provider-id</code> property.</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 13399040,
