    "last_activity_date" : 1735025892,
    "creation_date" : 1735025892,
    "answer_id" : 79305014,
    "question_id" : 68473460,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If your account doesn't have the necessary permissions to get the issuer ID from the integrations tab, or wherever else, Nathan shared a great way</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>HTML Inspection: Click your profile in the top-right corner. Once the drop down popup appears, HTML inspect it and search for the target account's data-provider-id property.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Here's his answer: <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/78924686/9669133\">https://stackoverflow.com/a/78924686/9669133</a></p>\n<p>It's right at the bottom of his answer - worked for me.</p>\n"
  } ],
